catchSetUpError

protected void catchSetUpError(SQLException error)
                        throws SQLException
Description copied from class: SqlVendor
Catches the given error thrown in SqlVendor.setUp(com.psddev.dari.db.SqlDatabase) to be processed in vendor-specific way. Typically, this is used to ignore errors when the vendor doesn't natively support that ability (e.g. CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS). The default implementation always rethrows the error.
